  "body": "## Issue\r\n\r\ntruffle-core's `cli.js` does a lot of `require`ing!\r\n\r\n<details>\r\n  <summary>See <code>require()</code> graph.</summary>\r\n  <img src=\"https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/151065/58066000-9ee8bc00-7b55-11e9-970f-7ff17b3dd236.png\" />\r\n</details>\r\n\r\n## Steps to Reproduce\r\n\r\nRun `truffle`.\r\n\r\nGenerate this graph with the following command (using [madge](https://github.com/pahen/madge)):\r\n```sh\r\n$ madge \\\r\n    --json \\\r\n    --includeNpm \\\r\n    --rankdir=LR \\\r\n  packages/truffle-core/cli.js \\\r\n    | sed -E 's/\"([a-z])/\"\\.\\/\\1/g' \\\r\n    | sed 's/\"\\.\\.\\/\\.\\.\\/node_modules\\//\"/g' \\\r\n    | madge --stdin --image deps.png --no-color\r\n```\r\n\r\n## Expected Behavior\r\n\r\n`cli.js` should require as little as possible, to make startup time fast, as well as to isolate problems with node_modules that can't be found in commands that aren't invoked.\r\n\r\nAlso, `require(\"web3\")` probably shouldn't be happening at startup every time.",
